48
00:01:35,639 --> 00:01:40,444
♪ HELP ME TO BREATHE. ♪

49
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:02,466
- ( persone chattando )

50
00:02:09,339 --> 00:02:12,376
- Girl: ENTONCES TU TAMBIEN QUIERES SUFRIR, VERDAD?

51
00:02:12,376 --> 00:02:14,344
QUIERES QUE TU CORAZON
TO FEEL

52
00:02:14,344 --> 00:02:16,380
LIKE IT'S BEEN SCRAPED ACROSS
WITH A RASP?

53
00:02:16,380 --> 00:02:19,483
SI ES ASI, NO MIRES PARA OTRO LADO, PASE LO QUE PASE.

54
00:02:31,261 --> 00:02:32,963
- ESTA BIEN.

55
00:02:37,367 --> 00:02:41,071
NADIE PUEDE ESTAR SEGURO DE SI REALMENTE EXISTE O NO.

56
00:02:41,071 --> 00:02:42,940
YA VERAS, EN SU MAYOR PARTE,

57
00:02:42,940 --> 00:02:45,175
IT DOESN'T REALLY MATTER TO
THE USER IF GOD ACTUALLY EXISTS

58
00:02:45,175 --> 00:02:47,177
IN THE WIRED.
PREGUNTALES. NO LES IMPORTA.

59
00:02:47,177 --> 00:02:49,313
UH, HEY, JUST A SECOND
THERE, LAIN.

60
00:02:49,313 --> 00:02:52,149
BEFORE YOU GO, LET ME TAKE
THIS GUY OUT FIRST.

61
00:02:54,117 --> 00:02:56,720
- QUE TIENE DE DIVERTIDO ESTO, TARO?

62
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:59,423
TODO LO QUE HAS HECHO ES MATAR A TODOS LOS OTROS JUGADORES.

63
00:02:59,423 --> 00:03:02,125
- NOBODY REALLY KNOWS
QUE ES DIVERTIDO.

64
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:04,428
AND SO NO ONE CAN REALLY
UNDERSTAND WHY.

65
00:03:07,331 --> 00:03:09,066
- HMM.

66
00:03:10,534 --> 00:03:12,536
THE NAME THAT WAS WRITTEN
ON THE DOOR PLATE WAS

67
00:03:12,536 --> 00:03:14,538
"TACHIBANA GENERAL
LABORATORIES."

68
00:03:25,282 --> 00:03:27,985
- ( voz masculina ) A COMPANY
AS BIG AS TACHIBANA GENERAL LABS

69
00:03:27,985 --> 00:03:30,120
WOULD NEVER DREAM
OF DOING ANYTHING ILLEGAL.

70
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,755
I'VE HEARD SOME RUMORS
THOUGH.

71
00:03:31,755 --> 00:03:33,290
- RUMORES?

72
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:36,293
- IN THE WIRED,
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA

73
00:03:36,293 --> 00:03:38,996
HOW WE'RE ABLE TO EXCHANGE
INFORMATION LIKE THIS?

74
00:03:38,996 --> 00:03:41,498
- OH, SO YOU THINK
ME ESTAS PROBANDO, NO?

75
00:03:41,498 --> 00:03:44,267
I KNOW YOU'RE TALKING
ABOUT THE I.P., AREN'T YOU?

76
00:03:44,267 --> 00:03:47,471
- ( risa )
PERDON, TIENES RAZON.

77
00:03:47,471 --> 00:03:49,473
WE RARELY KNOW OF
THE PROTOCOL'S EXISTENCE,

78
00:03:49,473 --> 00:03:51,675
ESPECIALLY WITH
THE ADVANCED LEVELS.

79
00:03:51,675 --> 00:03:54,211
HOWEVER, THE SIXTH-GEN PROTOCOL
HAS REACHED

80
00:03:54,211 --> 00:03:58,181
ITS ABSOLUTE DATA THROUGHPUT
LIMIT, AS FAR AS WE CAN TELL.

81
00:03:58,181 --> 00:04:02,419
- ENTONCES ES EL PROTOCOLO DE SEPTIMA GENERACION.

82
00:04:02,419 --> 00:04:06,156
- YES, THE SEVENTH-GEN PROTOCOL.
BIG COMPANIES ARE THE ONES

83
00:04:06,156 --> 00:04:08,158
MAKING IT INTO
THE NEW INFRASTRUCTURE.

84
00:04:08,158 --> 00:04:10,160
YA VERAS, CONTROLAR
THE PROTOCOL

85
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,596
MEANS TO CONTROL THE ENTIRE
ECONOMY OF THE WIRED

86
00:04:12,596 --> 00:04:14,531
WITHOUT ANY INTERFERENCE.

87
00:04:14,531 --> 00:04:17,401
ESCUCHO QUE HAY CONSTANTES
SABOTAGE ATTEMPTS GOING ON.

88
00:04:17,401 --> 00:04:20,037
AND THE PARTY
BEHIND ALL THIS IS...

89
00:04:21,038 --> 00:04:23,206
- LABORATORIOS GENERALES TACHIBANA.

90
00:04:24,474 --> 00:04:26,543
- ( risa )

91
00:04:44,194 --> 00:04:46,329
- ESTAS BIEN, MIKA?

92
00:04:46,329 --> 00:04:49,066
- YO-- YO--
( murmurando )

93
00:04:52,502 --> 00:04:54,504
( mumbling )

94
00:05:59,302 --> 00:06:02,472
- MOMMY, DADDY,

95
00:06:02,472 --> 00:06:04,441
CAN I ASK--?

96
00:06:07,277 --> 00:06:09,279
A WHILE AGO SOME--

97
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:12,382
SOMEBODY ASKED ME
A STRANGE QUESTION.

98
00:06:12,382 --> 00:06:15,385
ME PREGUNTARON,
"ERES LAIN IWAKURA?"

99
00:06:15,385 --> 00:06:17,387
AND THEN THEY ALSO
WANTED TO KNOW,

100
00:06:17,387 --> 00:06:19,456
"ARE YOUR PARENTS
REALMENTE TUS PADRES?"

101
00:06:19,456 --> 00:06:22,292
NO ES GRACIOSO?

102
00:06:22,292 --> 00:06:24,861
ES GRACIOSO, NO?

103
00:06:24,861 --> 00:06:27,731
LA GENTE DICE LAS COSAS MAS GRACIOSAS, NO?

104
00:06:29,599 --> 00:06:31,301
VERDAD?

105
00:07:14,477 --> 00:07:16,913
- ( chicas chattando )
- OH MY GOSH, YOU LOOK SO GOOD.

106
00:07:16,913 --> 00:07:20,684
Girls: HEY.  SO GOOD
TO SEE YOU.

107
00:07:20,684 --> 00:07:22,686
VAS A IR A VER
THIS MOVIE AFTERWARDS?

108
00:07:22,686 --> 00:07:24,454
- EH?

109
00:07:24,454 --> 00:07:25,622
OH, HI, ALICE.

110
00:07:25,622 --> 00:07:27,490
GOOD MORNING.

111
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:32,696
QUE PASA?
QUE PASA, ALICE? DIME.

112
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:39,402
- NO SE.
SOLO QUE NO LO CREO.

113
00:07:39,402 --> 00:07:41,671
- EH?  WHAT?

114
00:07:41,671 --> 00:07:43,440
BELIEVE WHAT?

115
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:46,443
- LAIN, TU NO LO HICISTO.

116
00:07:46,443 --> 00:07:49,813
- NO HICE QUE?  EH?

117
00:07:49,813 --> 00:07:52,415
- APUESTO QUE HA ESTADO ACTUANDO DE INOCENTE SOLA.

118
00:07:52,415 --> 00:07:54,718
- REIKA, NO LO SABES
FOR SURE.

119
00:07:54,718 --> 00:07:58,021
- EN SERIO, QUIERES DECIR QUE NO FUE TU, LAIN?

120
00:07:58,021 --> 00:08:01,424
- WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

121
00:08:01,424 --> 00:08:04,327
- LAIN, EN EL WIRED,
TU--?

122
00:08:10,734 --> 00:08:12,736
NO, NEVER MIND.

123
00:08:12,736 --> 00:08:14,904
FORGET ABOUT IT.
IT COULDN'T HAVE BEEN YOU, LAIN.

124
00:08:17,674 --> 00:08:21,645
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I TRUST YOU, OKAY?

125
00:08:21,645 --> 00:08:23,647
- UH, ALICE.
- EH?

126
00:08:26,716 --> 00:08:27,884
( gasps )

127
00:08:47,837 --> 00:08:50,740
- HEY, ALICE.
- ( girls laughing )

128
00:09:21,104 --> 00:09:23,640
- ( voces susurrando )

129
00:09:25,408 --> 00:09:27,610
- ( voz masculina )
IT'S JUST TOO DANGEROUS.

130
00:09:27,610 --> 00:09:29,679
WE HAVE TO AVOID
APPROVING ANY MORE BILLS.

131
00:09:29,679 --> 00:09:31,414
- ( voz femenina )
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.

132
00:09:31,414 --> 00:09:32,916
HOW COULD SUCH A NICE GUY
GET HIMSELF INTO

133
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:34,851
SUCH A COLLECTION
OF WEIRD STUFF?

134
00:09:34,851 --> 00:09:36,553
- ( voz masculina )
THERE'S AN EXTREMELY SERIOUS BUG

135
00:09:36,553 --> 00:09:38,054
THAT HAS BEEN DETECTED
IN PROTOCOL SIX.

136
00:09:38,054 --> 00:09:40,790
EL DAÑO CAUSADO POR ESTO PUEDE SER CATASTROFICO EN EL WIRED.

137
00:09:40,790 --> 00:09:42,826
- YOU HAVEN'T HEARD
THE BEST PART-- EVERY NIGHT

138
00:09:42,826 --> 00:09:45,061
A CHILDLIKE PERSON IN
A RED-AND-GREEN STRIPED SWEATER

139
00:09:45,061 --> 00:09:47,497
APPEARS IN HER ROOM.
- WHEN SHE WAS IN HIGH SCHOOL,

140
00:09:47,497 --> 00:09:49,733
THAT POP SINGER HIT SOMEONE
WITH HER BOYFRIEND'S CAR.

141
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:51,134
AND THEN SHE JUST
FLED THE SCENE.

142
00:09:51,134 --> 00:09:52,635
- I TELL YOU THAT
IT'S GOTTA BE TRUE.

143
00:09:52,635 --> 00:09:54,537
I HEARD ALL THE INFORMATION
FIRSTHAND.

144
00:09:54,537 --> 00:09:57,874
- ( risa ) THE BUILDING'S
A FAMOUS HAUNTED SPOT, YOU KNOW?

145
00:09:57,874 --> 00:09:59,876
IF YOU LOOK AT ITS TERMINAL
AT NIGHT,

146
00:09:59,876 --> 00:10:01,678
INTERNAL EMAIL SHOWS UP,
BUT NOBODY'S THERE.

147
00:10:01,678 --> 00:10:03,079
- THE KNIGHTS
DON'T EXIST.

148
00:10:03,079 --> 00:10:05,115
SOME AMERICAN STUDENT
STARTED IT AS A JOKE.

149
00:10:05,115 --> 00:10:07,784
- CALLATE!
A QUIEN LE IMPORTA ESO?

150
00:10:07,784 --> 00:10:11,154
- ( voz masculina ) DON'T YOU FIND
ANY OF IT INTERESTING?

151
00:10:11,154 --> 00:10:13,556
- EH?  WHO'S THERE?

152
00:10:15,492 --> 00:10:18,895
- ME ESTAS BUSCANDO, LAIN, NO ES ASI?

153
00:10:18,895 --> 00:10:21,631
- ENTONCES DIOS HACE SU GRAN ENTRADA.

154
00:10:21,631 --> 00:10:24,167
- PERO COMO DEFINES A TU DIOS?

155
00:10:24,167 --> 00:10:27,504
IF IT'S THE CREATOR
OF THE WORLD, THAT'S NOT ME.

156
00:10:27,504 --> 00:10:29,739
THE ALL-POWERFUL RULER
OF THE WORLD?

157
00:10:29,739 --> 00:10:32,842
SURELY YOU ARE MISTAKEN.
YOU GIVE GOD TOO MUCH CREDIT.

158
00:10:32,842 --> 00:10:34,744
- ENTONCES DONDE ESTAS TU?

159
00:10:34,744 --> 00:10:37,414
- WELL, IF YOU DEFINE GOD

160
00:10:37,414 --> 00:10:40,650
AS ONE WHO EXISTS EVERYWHERE
IN THAT OTHER WORLD OUT THERE--

161
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:43,119
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU MEAN,
THEN YES,

162
00:10:43,119 --> 00:10:45,121
I SUPPOSE THAT
YOU COULD CALL ME THAT.

163
00:10:45,121 --> 00:10:47,123
I HAVE ONLY
A SLIGHT INFLUENCE

164
00:10:47,123 --> 00:10:49,125
ON THE OVERALL WORKINGS
OF THE WORLD, HOWEVER.

165
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:50,860
- QUIEN DIABLOS ERES TU?

166
00:10:50,860 --> 00:10:52,896
- I AM YOU.

167
00:10:52,896 --> 00:10:55,865
SURELY YOU MUST HAVE
REALIZED IT SOMETIME--

168
00:10:55,865 --> 00:10:57,867
THAT ANOTHER YOU
HAS ALWAYS EXISTED

169
00:10:57,867 --> 00:10:59,869
ON ITS OWN TERMS
HERE IN THE WIRED.

170
00:10:59,869 --> 00:11:02,872
TU ERES MERAMENTE UN HOLOGRAMA DE ESE OTRO TU.

171
00:11:02,872 --> 00:11:05,842
ERES ESENCIALMENTE SOLO UN CUERPO.

172
00:11:05,842 --> 00:11:08,912
- ESPERAS QUE ME LO CREA?

173
00:11:10,747 --> 00:11:12,849
IMPOSIBLE.
ES LOCURA.

174
00:11:12,849 --> 00:11:14,851
- ( risa )

175
00:11:14,851 --> 00:11:16,986
BUT YOU DON'T THINK
THAT THE YOU IN THE REAL WORLD

176
00:11:16,986 --> 00:11:18,988
IS THE SAME
AS THE ONE

177
00:11:18,988 --> 00:11:20,990
THAT'S STANDING HERE
IN THE WIRED, DO YOU?

178
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:22,992
- WELL, NO.

179
00:11:22,992 --> 00:11:26,229
BECAUSE I'M ME.
I'M ME.

180
00:11:53,723 --> 00:11:56,159
- ( dispositivo vibrando )

181
00:11:56,020 --> 00:11:59,070
Tommy el Voyeur

182
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:07,330
Tommy el Voyeur

183
00:13:04,027 --> 00:13:06,596
- ALICE.

184
00:13:06,596 --> 00:13:09,699
ALICE, WHERE ARE YOU?

185
00:13:10,700 --> 00:13:12,235
ALICE.

186
00:13:12,235 --> 00:13:16,873
ALICE.
ALICE, DONDE ESTAS?

187
00:13:19,242 --> 00:13:21,744
ALICE, WHERE ARE YOU?

188
00:13:21,744 --> 00:13:23,046
ALICE?

189
00:13:25,281 --> 00:13:28,117
WHAT DID I--
WHAT DID I DO?

190
00:13:28,117 --> 00:13:30,853
WHAT DID I DO
IN THE WIRED?

191
00:13:30,853 --> 00:13:35,024
QUE ESTA HACIENDO EL OTRO YO MIENTRAS ESTOY SENTADA AQUI?

192
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:48,260
NO TE PREOCUPES POR LOS RUMORES! NO TE PREOCUPES!

193
00:14:38,921 --> 00:14:40,923
- ARE YOU SURE
IT IS ALL RIGHT

194
00:14:40,923 --> 00:14:42,992
FOR YOU TO BE DOING THIS
WITH A TEACHER?

195
00:14:42,992 --> 00:14:44,827
- NO, IT'S NOT.

196
00:14:44,827 --> 00:14:46,963
- SO THEN WHY ARE YOU
DOING IT?

197
00:14:46,963 --> 00:14:48,965
WON'T YOU GET
INTO TROUBLE?

198
00:14:48,965 --> 00:14:51,034
- PORQUE QUIERO.

199
00:14:52,402 --> 00:14:53,936
( gasps )

200
00:15:02,679 --> 00:15:04,947
- ( risita )

201
00:15:15,825 --> 00:15:18,227
QUE VERGUENZA, ALICE.

202
00:15:18,227 --> 00:15:21,864
DIME, TIENES ALGUNA IDEA DE QUIEN LE GUSTA A ALICE MIZUKI?

203
00:15:25,401 --> 00:15:28,137
AND DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHO SHE'S THINKING OF

204
00:15:28,137 --> 00:15:30,339
WHEN SHE PLAYS
WITH HERSELF?

205
00:15:32,075 --> 00:15:33,710
- THEY WERE RIGHT.

206
00:15:33,710 --> 00:15:35,712
IT WAS YOU WHO TOLD
EVERYONE, WASN'T IT?

207
00:15:35,712 --> 00:15:37,880
THE RUMORS THAT WERE GOING
AROUND SCHOOL WERE TRUE.

208
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,982
- ( risita )

209
00:15:39,982 --> 00:15:41,984
- LAIN!

210
00:15:41,984 --> 00:15:44,954
YOU'VE ALWAYS BEEN SITTING THERE
QUIETLY, JUST WATCHING ME.

211
00:15:44,954 --> 00:15:47,190
VISTE LO QUE NO QUERIA QUE NADIE SUPIERA SOBRE

212
00:15:47,190 --> 00:15:50,159
CUANDO NO QUERIA QUE NADIE VIERA LO QUE HACIA AQUI.

213
00:15:50,159 --> 00:15:52,995
AND THEN WHEN I--
- ( riendo )

214
00:15:52,995 --> 00:15:55,498
- TELL ME.  IT CAN'T BE.
LAIN, TELL ME.

215
00:15:55,498 --> 00:15:57,200
LAIN.

216
00:15:59,168 --> 00:16:01,170
YOU DECEIVED ME!

217
00:16:18,855 --> 00:16:21,424
- ( música animada sonando )

218
00:16:42,545 --> 00:16:44,914
- ( riendo )

219
00:16:48,351 --> 00:16:51,854
- WHO ARE YOU?

220
00:16:51,854 --> 00:16:54,223
YOU'RE NOT ME.
THERE'S JUST NO WAY.

221
00:16:54,223 --> 00:16:56,959
I'D NEVER DO THE KIND OF THINGS
THAT YOU'VE BEEN DOING.

222
00:16:56,959 --> 00:16:59,362
- OH, SPARE ME.
- JUST STOP IT.

223
00:16:59,362 --> 00:17:01,898
WHY ARE YOU ACTING LIKE
THE PART OF ME THAT I HATE?

224
00:17:01,898 --> 00:17:04,233
I WISH YOU WOULD
JUST GO AWAY.

225
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:06,936
- ( risita )

226
00:17:12,275 --> 00:17:14,110
- TE VOY A MATAR.

227
00:17:16,145 --> 00:17:19,849
- LOOK AT ME.
I'M COMMITTING SUICIDE.

228
00:17:19,849 --> 00:17:22,118
( laughing )

229
00:17:23,586 --> 00:17:27,089
- POR QUE-- POR QUE ESTAS TAN CALIENTE?

230
00:17:27,089 --> 00:17:30,226
WHY IS IT?  WHY DO I HAVE
TO FEEL YOUR BODY HEAT?

231
00:17:30,226 --> 00:17:32,895
IS THERE NO ESCAPING YOU?
- BUT HOW CAN YOU?

232
00:17:32,895 --> 00:17:35,565
SOY LAIN COMO TU LO ERES, NO ES ASI?

233
00:17:35,565 --> 00:17:38,201
- NO!  NO!

234
00:17:38,201 --> 00:17:40,903
- ( riendo )

235
00:17:58,087 --> 00:18:00,890
- QUE DIABLOS?
QUE SON ELLOS?

236
00:18:02,058 --> 00:18:03,960
- ( voz masculina )
THEY'RE ALL YOU.

237
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:06,963
I SAID THAT YOU'VE ALWAYS
EXISTED IN THE WIRED, DIDN'T I?

238
00:18:06,963 --> 00:18:10,066
- YES.
- YOU'RE EXACTLY THE SAME AS ME.

239
00:18:10,066 --> 00:18:12,268
YOU'RE OMNIPRESENT
IN THE WIRED

240
00:18:12,268 --> 00:18:14,003
FOREVER.

241
00:18:14,003 --> 00:18:16,138
WHEREVER ANYONE IS,
WHEREVER THEY GO,

242
00:18:16,138 --> 00:18:18,274
YOU HAVE ALWAYS
BEEN THERE.

243
00:18:18,274 --> 00:18:22,311
HAS VISTO LO QUE NO PERMITIERON QUE LOS OTROS VIERAN.

244
00:18:22,311 --> 00:18:25,114
YOU'VE TOLD EVERYONE
ABOUT IT, THAT'S ALL.

245
00:18:25,114 --> 00:18:27,116
IT WAS THE RIGHT THING
TO DO.

246
00:18:27,116 --> 00:18:28,918
DON'T WORRY.

247
00:18:28,918 --> 00:18:32,455
THE WIRED'S INFORMATION
SHOULD BE SHARED, SHOULDN'T IT?

248
00:18:39,662 --> 00:18:43,299
- ALL OF IT--
ALL YOU'VE SAID--

249
00:18:43,299 --> 00:18:45,134
IT'S A LIE.

250
00:18:45,134 --> 00:18:47,503
- WHY IS THAT?
- ALICE AND ALL OF THE OTHERS--

251
00:18:47,503 --> 00:18:49,505
THEY SAID THAT THEY SAW ME
IN THE WIRED

252
00:18:49,505 --> 00:18:51,374
WHEN I KNOW
I WASN'T THERE.

253
00:18:51,374 --> 00:18:54,443
WHAT REALLY MATTERS IS THAT
AS LONG AS I'M AWARE OF MYSELF,

254
00:18:54,443 --> 00:18:58,915
MY TRUE SELF IS ALWAYS
RIGHT HERE INSIDE OF ME.

255
00:18:58,915 --> 00:19:00,917
YOU'RE TELLING ME
THAT YOU'VE BEEN PASSING OFF

256
00:19:00,917 --> 00:19:02,919
THESE DUPES AS ME
ALL ALONG?

257
00:19:02,919 --> 00:19:04,921
QUE MONTON DE BASURA.

258
00:19:07,356 --> 00:19:10,026
IF I'M REALLY--

259
00:19:10,026 --> 00:19:12,028
IF I'M REALLY
WHAT YOU SAY I AM,

260
00:19:12,028 --> 00:19:14,030
AND I'M TOTALLY DELUDED,
THEN--

261
00:19:14,030 --> 00:19:16,565
- ENTONCES QUE, LAIN?

262
00:19:18,100 --> 00:19:20,336
- ALL THEIR MEMORIES
OF BEING SEEN BY LAIN--

263
00:19:20,336 --> 00:19:22,705
I COULD PERHAPS DELETE
THAT INFORMATION.

264
00:19:25,074 --> 00:19:27,076
- THAT'S TRUE.

265
00:19:27,076 --> 00:19:28,577
GIVE IT A TRY.

266
00:19:28,577 --> 00:19:31,580
YOU WERE BORN WITH THAT KIND
OF POWER INSIDE OF YOU.

267
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:54,370
- ( chicas chattando, riendo )

268
00:19:58,007 --> 00:20:00,409
- Chica: ESTARE POR LOS CASILLEROS DESPUES.

269
00:20:00,409 --> 00:20:02,678
- Girl #2: NO, OF COURSE NOT.
- Girl #1: SEE YA.

270
00:20:02,678 --> 00:20:04,146
- Alice: LAIN!

271
00:20:06,682 --> 00:20:09,352
- ( risita )
- HEY LAIN, WAIT UP.

272
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,356
- ( voz de Lain ) COULD THEY
REALLY HAVE FORGOTTEN?

273
00:20:13,356 --> 00:20:16,025
- ( riendo )

274
00:20:16,025 --> 00:20:18,427
- OLVIDARON?

275
00:20:18,427 --> 00:20:21,230
- LAIN.

276
00:20:22,631 --> 00:20:25,034
- THEY REALLY DID.

277
00:20:25,034 --> 00:20:26,435
- ALICE.

278
00:20:30,406 --> 00:20:33,142
QU-- QUE?
QUE DIABLOS--?

279
00:20:33,142 --> 00:20:35,378
- ALICE.

280
00:20:35,378 --> 00:20:38,114
HEY, I WANT TO GO
TO CYBERIA TODAY.

281
00:20:38,114 --> 00:20:41,150
COME ON, LET'S GO.
- ( risita )

282
00:20:41,150 --> 00:20:44,086
- I SECOND.
- THIS IS UNUSUAL.

283
00:20:44,086 --> 00:20:47,023
- SURE, WE CAN GET CHANGED
AT MY PLACE AGAIN

284
00:20:47,023 --> 00:20:49,025
AND GO FROM THERE.
- GREAT.

285
00:20:53,562 --> 00:20:56,098
HEY, ALICE, QUE PIENSAS QUE DEBERIA USAR?

286
00:20:56,098 --> 00:20:59,268
- PARA ESTO!
ALICE, ESTOY AHI! SOY YO!

287
00:21:05,674 --> 00:21:08,377
I'M OVER HERE, ALICE.

288
00:21:08,377 --> 00:21:11,480
- Julie: COME ON, HURRY UP.
- Reika: HEY, WAIT FOR ME.

289
00:21:15,684 --> 00:21:17,787
- THAT'S RIGHT.
IT'S JUST LIKE YOU SAID--

290
00:21:17,787 --> 00:21:21,090
LAIN IS LAIN
AND I AM ME.

291
00:21:42,678 --> 00:21:44,680
- HOLA, NAVI.

292
00:21:45,714 --> 00:21:47,716
- HOLA, LAIN.

293
00:21:54,657 --> 00:21:56,659
- I AM ME.

294
00:21:56,659 --> 00:21:58,761
I'M THE ONLY ME, VERDAD?

295
00:21:58,761 --> 00:22:02,364
AND THERE ISN'T ANY OTHER ME
BUT ME.

296
00:22:02,364 --> 00:22:03,866
ISN'T THAT VERDAD?

297
00:22:15,811 --> 00:22:18,280
- ( canción temática sonando )

298
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:37,750
nan no tsumi mo nai hazu na no ni nanraka no batsu wo uketeru

299
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:37,750
Although I must be innocent, now I am punished

300
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:44,340
jibun de maita tane de mo nai no ni

301
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:44,340
I wasn't the one who sowed those seeds, but nevertheless

302
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:50,510
sakimidareta hana tsumasareru

303
00:22:44,340 --> 00:22:50,510
I have to pull up the flowers that bloomed from them

304
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,690
shiranai koto to mo ienai ga

305
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,690
I can't say I didn't know about it

306
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:06,150
katabou katsuida oboe wa nai

307
00:23:01,690 --> 00:23:06,150
but I don't remember taking any part in it

308
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:12,450
jiyuu wo takaku kawasareta ki mo suru ga

309
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:12,450
I think my freedom cost me dearly

310
00:23:12,870 --> 00:23:19,790
kokoro made yasuku utta oboe wa nai

311
00:23:12,870 --> 00:23:19,790
but I don't remember selling my soul so cheaply

312
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:27,800
hey hey kutabatte osaraba suru made

313
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:27,800
Hey hey, until I die and say farewell...

314
00:23:28,670 --> 00:23:37,560
hey hey dare no te ni mo kakaranai

315
00:23:28,670 --> 00:23:37,560
Hey hey... no one can touch me

316
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:43,150
tooi yoru wo urotsuiteiru

317
00:23:38,930 --> 00:23:43,150
You probably don't know

318
00:23:43,150 --> 00:23:52,160
shiranai darou eien no narazu monotachi wo

319
00:23:43,150 --> 00:23:52,160
the eternal outlaws prowling in the distant night
